body_html:
The problem may be due to the fact that the TF-SLIM effort focused on Python 2.7 and I'm using 3.5 on windows. I just tried the same TF-SLIM with TF 1.0 and many more issues, it seems few can keep up with all progress on TF and now with TF1.0 there have been more changes making TF1.0 compatibility with TF-SLIM more challenging. It seems we need a list stating with contrib/etc. is compatible what version of TF.

body:
The problem may be due to the fact that the TF-SLIM effort focused on
Python 2.7 and I'm using 3.5 on windows. I just tried the same TF-SLIM with
TF 1.0 and many more issues, it seems few can keep up with all progress on
TF and now with TF1.0 there have been more changes making TF1.0
compatibility with TF-SLIM more challenging. It seems we need a list
stating with contrib/etc. is compatible what version of TF.
